  <preparation>Mix together oats, sugars, flour, salt and baking soda.  Mix in eggs, corn oil, water, honey and vanilla.  Add remaining ingredients and mix one final time.

Spoon dough out into double spoonfulls or -- if you're sloppy like me - 1/4 cups -- and top each with pecan and 1 teaspoon of honey.

Cook 14-18 minutes at 350F degrees.</preparation>
